    "details": {
      "blurb": "Arbiter of Allegiance — the Gray Maiden indoctrinator (A52/A56)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "elven",
          "infernal",
          "shoanti",
          "varisian",
          "vudrani"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 10
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (A52/A56):</strong> the Gray Maidens' <strong>Arbiter of Allegiance</strong> — Cressida task #6's 'mysterious indoctrinator.' An embittered Acadamae enchanter who co-designed the Maidens' conditioning (torture, blackmail, mind-control), clashed with Sabina, and commands the castle Maidens once Sabina defects. She is <strong>Ishani Dhatri's sister</strong>: she lured him into the castle by answering his <em>sendings</em>, ambushed him in the chapel (A13), and fed his soul to the @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.ch6Akaruzug00001]{akaruzug} (A18). Confronted about him — or facing his raised, returned self — she laughs that Togomor will simply have to build her brother's soul a new 'house.' <strong>Morale:</strong> <em>dimension door</em> to A56 if the false Ileosa melts or she drops below ~40 HP; grabs her spellbooks and flees the castle to shelter with the Arkonas.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
